article_title: Despite some 2014 successes, tea party is fading as a brand
article_text: He’s just the kind of candidate the tea party likes: deeply conservative, an outsider and a challenge to the Washington establishment. Yet Chris McDaniel rarely utters the words “tea party” as he campaigns against Sen. Thad Cochran, R-Miss., for the GOP Senate nomination.
